<p>Hi <span class="citation" data-cites="jts1882">@jts1882</span> – thanks for this helpful suggestion. It’s a good idea to enable direct links to higher-level taxonomic views on the MDD taxonomy. I’ll copy <span class="citation" data-cites="liphardt">@liphardt</span> here to flag this as a priority area for work. It would be excellent to have MDD-curated information flowing more readily into Wikipedia pages. Cheers. I’ve finally worked out how to use github* and have made the appropriate changes in my fork of the project.</p>
<p>Use search parameter on the search species page to initialise the “filter” text in the search box:</p>
<ul>
<li>List of cats in genus <em>Felis</em>: https://jts1882.github.io/mdd/explore.html#search=Felis</li>
</ul>
<p>Use order, family and genus parameters to initialize state on taxonomy page.</p>
<ul>
<li>Use order parameter to expand order content (show families): https://jts1882.github.io/mdd/taxa.html#order=Carnivora</li>
<li>Use family parameter to expand family content (show genera): https://jts1882.github.io/mdd/taxa.html#family=Felidae</li>
<li>Use genus parameter to expand genus content (show species): https://jts1882.github.io/mdd/taxa.html#genus=Felis</li>
</ul>
<p>This is mainly done by adding new functions. The exceptions are a modification of goPermalink() to handle seeding the search box and addition of a single line to call the function that expands the content at the end of the complete block in createOrderTable(), fillFamily() and fillGenus().</p>
<p>The new functions are:</p>
<ul>
<li>parseURLforParameters() - gets the parameters from the url</li>
<li>initializeOrderExpansion() - expands the order to show families; called at the end of createOrderTable()</li>
<li>initializeFamilyExpansion() - expands the family to show genera; called at the end of fillFamily()</li>
<li>initializeGenusExpansion() - expands the genus to show species; called at the end of fillGenus()</li>
<li>expandTaxon() - expands the list by creating a click event for the appropriate button, which then initiates fillFamily(), fillGenus() or fillSpecies()</li>
<li>getParentTaxon() - gets higher taxa for families and genera so they can be expanded. You need to expand the order before expanding the family and expanding the genus needs both order and family expanded</li>
</ul>
<p>If you don’t use any parameters, nothing should be different.</p>
<p>_* The main problem getting the fork to work was format of the internal urls. Links such as “/assets/data/mdd.csv” or “/js/filter.js” don’t work in the fork and need the leading slash removed (i.e. “assets/data/mdd.csv” or “js/filter.js”). I don’t think the slash is needed in the master project. This is really great <span class="citation" data-cites="jts1882">@jts1882</span> – thanks for your effort in adding this functionality on your fork of the project. Sorry it took a while for our team to get back to this. I’m looking at your code now, and it seems that the main new functions are here (https://github.com/jts1882/mdd/blob/master/js/mammals.js) – is that right?</p>
