<p>Phyllotis rupestris (-) – Hmm, I hadn’t realized this. I’m going to do some more investigation over the next few days, but may choose to go with your conclusion in the end. Phyllotis is a rough genus at the moment.</p>
<p>Rhipidomys bezerrensis and R. caracolensis (-) – I don’t know why I added these species so prematurely… I can’t decide whether to leave them with comments to them being in pre-publication or remove them yet. Because I’m sure they’ll be described soon and removing them for one version seems a bit ridiculous, but I generally wouldn’t add them until they were officially described.</p>
