<p>Just a quick note on what I’m accepting onto the next MDD version for now. The nomenclature ones I am leaving as they are on the MDD for now, given that many of these should probably be published before making a change that will effect researchers widely. For the first set you recommended though, I have included all of the changes you suggested. (New post because the previous one is getting very long)</p>
<h4 id="different-people-1">Different people</h4>
<ul>
<li>Kuhl (1 differences)
<ul>
<li>Kuhl (MDD) vs. Maximilian zu Wied (Prince of Wied; German naturalist; checked; german) (tried: M. Wied, M. zu Wied, Wied, zu Wied) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1000775; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/26304">Brachyteles hypoxanthus</a>; Author 1; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/38738">Wied (1820)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>Attribution to Wied follows: Garbino, G.S.T. and Costa, H.C. 2015. Some nomenclatural notes regarding authorship and dates of New World monkeys (Primates: Platyrrhini). Sherbornia 2(3):21-27. URL: http://hbs.bishopmuseum.org/dating/sherbornia/issues/s02-03.pdf</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Leisler (1 differences)
<ul>
<li>Leisler (MDD) vs. Heinrich Kuhl (1797–1821; German naturalist; checked; german) (tried: H. Kuhl, Kuhl) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1005375; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/11028">Myotis bechsteinii</a>; Author 1; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/60595">Kuhl (1817)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>It seems clear from the original description that Kuhl, not Leisler, was responsible for making the name available, though Leisler originally discovered it.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h4 id="k">K</h4>
<ul>
<li>K. G. Heller (2 differences)
<ul>
<li>K. G. Heller (MDD) vs. Klaus-Gerhard Heller (German mammalogist; checked; german) (tried: Heller, K.-G. Heller) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1005360; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/10978">Myotis alcathoe</a>; Author 2; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/1993">Helversen et al. (2001)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>K. G. Heller (MDD) vs. Klaus-Gerhard Heller (German mammalogist; checked; german) (tried: Heller, K.-G. Heller) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1004702; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/40797">Rhinolophus luctoides</a>; Author 6; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/26606">Volleth et al. (2015)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>MDD cites him as “K.-G. Heller” on <em>Rhinolophus yonghoiseni</em>; I’d prefer to use that authorship throughout</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
