<li>L. von Bohmann (MDD) vs. Ludwig Bohmann (unchecked; german) (tried: Bohmann, L. Bohmann) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1003419; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/30694">Otomys zinki</a>; Author 1; authority)</li>
<li>I only have one paper by him, but there his name is given without the “von”.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Le Conte (2 differences)
<ul>
<li>Le Conte (MDD) vs. John Lawrence LeConte (1825–1883; American entomologist; checked; general) (tried: J. L. LeConte, J. Lawrence LeConte, J. LeConte, J.L. LeConte, LeConte) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1001871; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/37436">Heterogeomys hispidus</a>; Author 1; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/35612">LeConte (1852)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>Le Conte (MDD) vs. John Lawrence LeConte (1825–1883; American entomologist; checked; general) (tried: J. L. LeConte, J. Lawrence LeConte, J. LeConte, J.L. LeConte, LeConte) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1001895; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/37823">Dipodomys heermanni</a>; Author 1; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/20718">LeConte (1853)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>There are two different Le Contes and MDD should probably add initials: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Eatton_Le_Conte (who named <em>Myosciurus pumilio</em> and <em>Antrozous pallidus</em>), https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Lawrence_LeConte (who named the two species above). They weren’t terribly consistent in writing their name as one or two words; I follow Wikipedia in using one word for J.L. and two words for J.E.</li>
</ul></li>
