<h3 id="different-authors">Different authors</h3>
<ul>
<li>Natterer (1 differences)
<ul>
<li>Natterer (MDD) vs. Heinrich Kuhl (1797–1821; German naturalist; checked; german) (tried: H. Kuhl, Kuhl) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1005135; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/10518">Miniopterus schreibersii</a>; Author 1; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/60595">Kuhl (1817)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>Similar situation to <em>Myotis bechsteinii</em>, Natterer gave the name but Kuhl actually described the species</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Sturt (1 differences)
<ul>
<li>Sturt (MDD) vs. John Gould (1804–1881; English ornithologist; checked; general) (tried: Gould, J. Gould) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1003188; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/30409">Leporillus conditor</a>; Author 1; authority)</li>
<li>Jackson &amp; Groves (2015:194) discuss why Gould should be cited as the author, not Sturt.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="different-order">Different order</h3>
<ul>
<li>McKenzie (1 differences)
<ul>
<li>McKenzie (MDD) vs. T.B. Reardon (unchecked; unspecified) (tried: Reardon, T. B. Reardon, T. Reardon, T.B. Reardon) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1005249; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/42130">Ozimops kitcheneri</a>; Author 2; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/29469">Reardon et al. (2014)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>The paper gives the authorship for this name as “McKenzie, Reardon &amp; Adams”, but MDD uses “Reardon, McKenzie, &amp; M. Adams”</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Rabarivola (1 differences)
<ul>
<li>Rabarivola (MDD) vs. Dietmar Zinner (unchecked; unspecified) (tried: D. Zinner, Zinner) (Hesperomys) (MDD#1001032; <a href="https://hesperomys.com/t/27115">Lepilemur sahamalaza</a>; Author 4; original citation: <a href="https://hesperomys.com/a/59528">Andriaholinirina et al. (2017)</a>; authority)</li>
<li>This paper has a ton of authors and MDD switches a few around. It should be “Andriaholinirina, Fausser, Roos, Zinner, Thalmann, Rabarivola, Ravoarimanana, Ganzhorn, Meier, Hilgartner, Walter, Zaramody, Langer, Hahn, E. Zimmermann, Radespiel, Craul, Tomiuk, Tattersall &amp; Rumpler”</li>
</ul></li>
